A Nebraska-based power company spent $500,000 and raised that much again for 5,777 acres of Costa Rican forest to give to the national park system this year, in order to offset carbon dioxide emissions from a power plant under construction in Washington state.
But in the amount of time it takes you to read this sentence, more than two acres of rain forest will be destroyed.
Costa Rica, which witnessed massive deforestation, has managed to preserve about 20 percent of its wilderness and is in the vanguard for creating new, benign uses for the land.
